federal prisoners held in south florida said jim jones regional 
spokesman for the us bureau of prisons 
after noriega was moved kollin met with him at the prison 
our position is that he should not be at mcc kollin said 
afterward he should be at homestead air force base as a 
temporary measure because he is a prisoner of war and he should be 
at homestead only to await transfer to a neutral third country 
on friday us district judge william hoeveler ordered noriega 
