<TEXT>
the food and drug administration today 
approved the drug fluconazole as an alternative treatment for two 
fungal infections that afflict patients with aids cancer and other 
diseases that weaken the immune system 
the drug can be used for treating cryptococcal meningitis an 
inflammation of the brain and nervous system that can be fatal 
it also was approved for treating candidiasis an infection that 
causes sores in the mouth and throat the infection is present in 
80 percent to 90 percent of aids patients in advanced stages of the 
disease 
other drugs are available to treat these infections but they 
can cause serious adverse reactions the fda said 
fluconazole can also cause side effects including abdominal 
discomfort nausea and less commonly signs of liver damage in 
rare cases the drug has been associated with severe skin rashes 
and fatal hepatic necrosis a form of liver failure the fda said 
the drug will be marketed by pfizer inc under the trade name 
diflucan 
</TEXT>
