<TEXT>
a moderate earthquake jolted central new 
mexico strongly enough to rattle furniture this morning but no 
injuries were reported 
we felt the whole house shake said albert miranda of 
veguita a few miles from the quakes epicenter south of 
albuquerque it didnt last very long the chandelier shook but 
nothing was broken it was a fast shake 
the dog went wild barking in the house said albino salas 
jr of bernardo he was running all over the room 
pat jorgenson of the us geological survey in menlo park 
calif said the surveys national earthquake information center in 
golden colo measured the tremor at 45 on the richter scale 
the epicenter of the 616 am quake was 40 miles south of 
albuquerque almost exactly the same spot as one of the same 
magnitude on nov 28 1989 she said 
both quakes occurred along the rio grande rift which splits new 
mexico north to south paralleling the rio grande from colorado to 
el paso texas ms jorgenson said 
the last time before november that an earthquake struck the same 
area was july 1906 she said 
allan sanford a professor of geophysics at the new mexico 
institute of mining and technology in socorro said earthquakes are 
relatively rare in the state california he said has 100 times as 
much quake activity as new mexico 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographsan earthquake of 4 on the richter scale can cause 
moderate damage in the local area and 5 can cause considerable 
damage 
the earthquake that caused heavy damage in the san 
franciscooakland area on oct 17 measured 71 on the richter scale 
