poor leadership not racism was the 
main cause of a riot during a labor day weekend gathering of black 
college students an independent panel has concluded 
the panel concluded that race became a factor only after 
violence began between students and police according to a report 
published sunday by the virginianpilot and ledgerstar newspaper 
of norfolk 
two days of looting during a gathering of 100000 students from 
predominantly black universities and other young people last 
september cost taxpayers more than 1 million the violence during 
greekfest damaged 124 stores in virginia beach and 50 people 
were injured in clashes with police and national guardsmen 
jack gravely president of the state national association for 
the advancement of colored people said today that his group 
supports the basic findings and conclusion of the report 
gravely however said there were some holes in the report 
concerning the arrest and detention policies of the various law 
enforcement agencies involved 
i think the police departments were let off the hook 
were not finished with virginia beach he said 
according to the norfolk newspaper the labor day review 
commission determined that poor preparation failure of 
communication and criminal actions by a small percentage of the 
crowd were responsible for the violence 
the commissions report was to be formally presented to virginia 
beach officials this afternoon city officials have said they wont 
comment until the report is released officially at that time 
the report said most police officers acted responsibly and 
professionally but it urged officials to review films of the 
violence and consider disciplining officers who violated procedures 
we believe some arrests were mistakenly made a few officers 
used inappropriate force and some subjected residents and visitors 
alike to abusive language the newspaper quoted the commission 
report as saying 
once the violence began the report said race then became 
a way to differentiate potential friends and foes 
better preparations by city officials could have helped head off 
problems during the gathering the commission said 
we believe that city council and the mayor should have been 
more active and should have exerted greater leadership the 
report said 
that sounds like a pretty fair assessment l victor 
