lyndon larouche was transported nearly 1000 
miles to testify in the loanfraud trial of an associate but the 
defense monday decided against calling the imprisoned political 
extremist to the stand 
i didnt need his testimony because there was no dispute on 
the evidence i wanted him for said pat monaghan the attorney 
representing donald phau monaghan refused to say what evidence he 
was referring to 
larouche will be taken back to a federal prison in rochester 
minn 
roanoke county sheriffs department spokesman james robertson 
would not give a cost estimate for flying larouche from minnesota 
and keeping him in the county jail for nearly a week but he said 
the county expects to be reimbursed by either larouche or the 
defendant 
phau is one of 16 members of the larouche organization who were 
charged three years ago with violating the virginia securities act 
by selling and issuing promissory notes for five 
laroucheaffiliated organizations all of the cases involved 
telephone solicitations for loans 
larouche was convicted 13 months ago on federal charges of mail 
fraud conspiracy to commit mail fraud and conspiracy to defraud 
the internal revenue service he was sentenced to 15 years in 
prison 
