improvements expected under the fiscal 1991 spending plan that 
president bush sent congress on monday that number should rise to 
102 per 10000 for 1990 returns and 103 per 10000 for 1991 returns 
those figures do not include irs computer checks of the returns 
of the 40 million taxpayers who file returns based principally on 
income from wages interest and dividends goldberg said 
irs computers automatically check those returns to make sure 
they include all income reported by employers banks and brokers 
while those computer checks are not audits goldberg said they are 
very thorough 
