colombia where a crackdown on cocaine cartels has brought violent 
retaliation 19 million for peru the worlds largest coca leaf 
producer and 157 million for bolivia 
the estimated outlays for all international affairs categories 
foreign aid maintaining embassies and running the state department 
would be 182 billion in 1991 an effective increase of nearly 
12 percent 
the 1990 figure is estimated at 146 billion but has been 
artificially reduced by onetime income of 17 billion from early 
repayment of past military aid loans 
