<TEXT>
the constituent assembly proposed 
monday that this southwest african territory declare independence 
on march 21 ending 75 years of rule by south africa namibia is 
africas last colony 
the 72member assembly elected in november submitted the date 
to louis pienaar namibias south african administrator who is 
expected to approve an assembly vote on the proposal is planned on 
tuesday 
south africa captured namibia from the germans in 1915 in 
december 1988 it agreed to grant independence as part of a 
regional treaty that also calls for phased withdrawal of cuban 
troops from angola namibias northern neighbor more than 6000 
un military and civilian personnel have been supervising the 
transition process since last april 
the constituent assembly also has been debating a democratic 
westernstyle constitution and is to begin voting on the document 
tuesday articlebyarticle 
no major disagreements are expected because all leading parties 
represented in the assembly say they support the proposed 
constitution 
the draft constitution contains a declaration of fundamental 
rights including freedom of movement freedom of speech and 
freedom of the press it foresees a multiparty democracy regular 
elections an independent judiciary and an executive president 
limited to two fiveyear terms 
one provision that may lead to dissension allows for detention 
without trial during a state of emergency or in time of war an 
individual could be detained without charge if that person was 
deemed a clear and present danger to the security of the state 
swapo the leftist south west africa peoples organization which 
had fought a bush war for independence from south africa since 
1966 won 41 seats in the assembly and will form the first 
government swapo leader sam nujoma is expected to become namibias 
president 
the multiracial democratic turnhalle alliance which wants 
namibia to have a free enterprise economy has 21 seats five 
parties share the 10 remaining seats 
twothirds of the assembly or 48 members must approve each 
article of the constitution 
the south african defense force southwest africa territorial 
force and the southwest african police fought swapo in the 
northern part of the territory in a war that killed 20000 people 
mostly guerrillas over 23 years the last fighting in the country 
of about 15 million occurred in april 1989 at the outset of the 
unsupervised independence process that resulted in elections in 
november for the constituent assembly 
the territory is composed of sparsely populated areas the 
territory as large as france and west germany combined contains 
11 main ethnic groups including two mixedrace groups eight black 
groups and about 75000 whites 
the ovambo people who inhabit the relatively fertile northern 
region make up about half the population 
