veterans for problems in the loan system instead of its own 
mismanagement of the program 
cranston called the down payment feature the most 
objectionable feature of the budget proposal 
congress created the program in 1944 precisely to allow 
hundreds of thousands of veterans to purchase homes even though 
they could not come up with a downpayment he said the same 
need is here today 
