expenditures would fall in 1991 because of a projected decrease in 
interest rates 
while bush requests a 473 million increase in the pell grants 
program which provides money to college student over the current 
48 billion the budget seeks to cut the program next fall by 
665 million 
as a result about 14000 students receiving awards averaging 
