american jewish theater here and did one nbc childrens special 
and some commercials he says 
still he is supposed to be of the mtv generation only video 
spoken there why write plays 
sherman blames it on his early exposure to theater i think 
doing that really influenced by interest in writing plays all my 
thoughts came to be as stageplay ideas rather than as video 
ideas the stage really helped that 
his women and wallace the dark kind of comedy is about a 
young man whose mother died when he was 6 it concerns the 
characters efforts over a 12year period to relate to women and 
stop using humor as a defense in his dealings with them 
as is the case of many plays and novels this play is partly 
autobiographical says sherman who lives in livingston nj 
but it has a sadder reallife basis than most 
his mother he says committed suicide when he was 6 twelve 
years later having begun writing with one play given a staged 
reading at the young playwrights festival he started work on 
women and wallace 
i did it mostly to deal with my thoughts about my mom and to 
try to deal with it in a realistic way not try to make it a 
movieoftheweek treatment of suicide he says i tried to 
really get down to the stuff i went through 
he submitted it to the festival which has an age limit of 19 
for all applicants and was begun in 1981 by broadway composer 
stephen sondheim 
out of 600 submissions it was one of four chosen for 
production the reviews for the rookie were good sherman 
goodnaturedly professes not to know why the critics were kind 
maybe it was a good day for them or something 
delegates from american playhouse it produces for film 
public tv and theater came saw and bought it was the first 
young playwrights festival play the company ever has purchased 
davis says 
we thought it was outstanding we were very very impressed 
with it and we made the deal its as simple as that 
after bennington says sherman a theater major he may go to 
graduate school or continue acting and writing he has two new 
plays in mind and another he says will get a workshop tryout at the 
los angeles theatre center 
he also plans to give screenwriting a try but doubts he ever 
will call hollywood home i dont know about moving there he 
says amused at the idea i dont know about being attached to my 
car that much 
