<TEXT>
from time to time a suspect under the strain of 
questioning will confess to a crime he didnt commit heres a 
strange case in west virginia in which two men confessed to the 
same murders the first was freed and the second was tried and 
convicted now hes going to be tried a second time 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
a decade ago paul reggettz iii spent 11 
months behind bars after confessing that he murdered his wife and 
their two children he was freed after a former neighbor confessed 
to the same crime 
reggettz has spent the past 10 years struggling to rebuild his 
life painfully aware of the stares and whispers of those who still 
