<TEXT>
on any given night in prime time 
85 million of brazils 150 million people stare into their 
television screens eagerly consuming the fare offered up by 
85yearold roberto marinho and his tv globo network 
thats an astounding share of brazils potential viewing public 
of 100 million even those who say they hate what marinho stands 
for and want his network broken up cant resist the magnetic pull 
not only is it brazils largest network it is the largest in 
the third world and on a global basis is generally considered to 
rank fourth after nbc abc and cbs in the united states 
an average of 966 million americans watch tv each night 
according to ac nielsen co with the three major networks 
attracting 60 million of them 
thus roberto marinho and tv globo with a whopping 85 percent 
share of the brazilian audience soars into the ratings 
stratosphere 
the network has 15000 employees and 70 stations reaching nearly 
all of brazils 4000 cities and towns 
all of that however leaves some brazilians deeply worried that 
marinho has far too much influence for brazils good 
none of the three other brazilian networks independents or 
educational tv come near to competing with tv globos recognized 
quality or popularity 
president fidel castro of cuba is a fan although he would place 
himself at the opposite end of the ideological field from marinho 
castros addiction is a tv globo soapopera sold throughout latin 
america titled a escrava isaura isaura the slave 
tv globos soaps called novelas draw the largest number 
of viewers the network also attracts an audience with firstrun 
movies dubbed into portuguese such as raiders of the lost 
ark it offers sophisticated farranging news coverage first 
on the scene of fires floods bus crashes and cabinet resignations 
yet the cries often go up break up tv globo 
books magazine articles and politicians charge that so vast a 
tv network is simply too powerful most particularly in a country 
where millions barely can read and turn to television for 
information as well as entertainment 
the direct target of the criticism is the iconoclastic 
billionaire marinho who also has his hand in newspapers radio 
book and magazine publishing and communications systems 
critics charge that marinho uses his conglomerate to push a 
rightwing probusiness antipopulist political message 
marinho whose physical bearing belies his age by 15 or 20 
years doesnt deny it 
we openly supported the candidacy of fernando collor de 
mello marinho unabashedly told a group of reporters in rio de 
janeiro recently he was referring to the victor in brazilian 
elections in december the first free presidential vote in almost 
30 years 
conservative profree enterprise collor de mello defeated a 
marxistoriented opponent in a final runoff by a slim margin and is 
to take office march 15 
but when marinho asserted that his media conglomerate also gave 
time and space to competing candidates skeptics sharing a widely 
held belief that marinho ordered slanted coverage to favor collor 
de mello laughed aloud some walked out 
the silverhaired magnate envisions his media might with a 
proselytizing mission this is not the united states we have an 
obligation to reach not only the cultured people but also those of 
the lowest classes 
and indeed the first signs of modern progress in brazils 
wretched favelas or hillside slums often are tv aerials 
sprouting from the roofs of miserable shacks 
brazil cannot be governed with roberto marinho having the 
power he does says the leftistpopulist leonel brizola former 
governor of rio de janeiro and one of 21 candidates who ran for the 
presidency 
during his unsuccessful campaign brizola promised on the 
first morning of my first day in office i will reexamine the 
monopoly of the tv globo party the biggest party in brazil that 
network must be taken off the air 
brizola finished third and was eliminated from the deciding 
runoff 
tv globo is agile and efficient with a level of quality that 
makes it the leader in the ratings said professor jose marques 
de melo the head of the school of communications and arts at the 
university of sao paulo the nations largest and most prestigious 
learning center but its professional conduct during the 
elections left a lot to be desired 
brazil needs a code of ethics for news media marques de 
melo added 
ricardo kotscho the press spokesman for the losing presidential 
candidate in the finals luis inacio lula da silva said marinhos 
extremely successful newspaper o globo of rio de janeiro which 
openly endorsed color de mello lost all its credibility in the 
campaign and also its morals 
in his session with the newsmen marinho said a newspaper can 
support whomever it wants he added that o globo gave coverage to 
the other candidates even though he personally didnt like them 
i have been called a fascist marinho said but when i was 
young i boxed and practiced jiujitsu and karate i know how to 
hit as well as get hit 
marinho inherited the newspaper o globo the world after his 
father irineu marinho died just three weeks after founding the 
paper in 1925 he expanded into radio in the 1940s and now runs a 
moneymaking nationwide radio network 
tv globo went on the air in 1965 timelife broadcasting of the 
united states once held a minority interest in it leading to 
charges that tv globo was a mouthpiece for american 
imperialism but now the globo empire belongs exclusively to 
marinho his brothers and his sons 
tv globo spends lavishly to produce its primetime novelas 
which draw ratings of over 90 percent at home translated from the 
portuguese they are exported to the rest of latin america western 
europe scandinavia the middle east the orient and us 
spanishlanguage stations 
marinho lives in the best mogul style in a fabulous estate high 
in the hills overlooking rio near the famous christ the redeemer 
statue on corcovado peak 
the roberto marinho foundation finances free art exhibits and 
openair concerts and operas for brazils poor masses and also a 
televised adulteducation course that has given some 4 million 
brazilian dropouts a chance to acquire high schoolequivalency 
diplomas 
in 1964 when a rightwing military regime seized power and 
ruled for 21 years marinho and his media voices were solidly 
behind it 
brizola exiled during the military dictatorship but later 
granted amnesty says i am not against roberto marinho 
personally but in brazil an essential public service such as radio 
and television must be made more democratic 
marinhos response mr brizola can provoke me all he wants 
it wont do him any good 
married twice and recently estranged from his second wife 
marinho did not flinch when a reporter asked him about his current 
relationship with a rio society figure lily de carvalho an old 
flame from his younger days 
she is a widow and a free woman he said 
age does not interfere with companionship i dont drink i 
dont smoke i exercise i go underwater fishing without an 
aqualung i dont spend any sleepless nights 
</TEXT>
