feel rca human drama 
 
sometimes you can judge a record by its cover 
johnny indovina the singerleader of human drama poses on 
feel with bare chest beads and necklaces black nail polish 
and crucifix earring his face darkened by shadows his hair 
hanging in front of his eyes like a mask 
this is music for the white makeup black leather and big 
moussed hair set its gloom and doom rock with plenty of angst 
thrown in 
feel is this los angelesbased groups first album its 
similar in tone to the smiths joy division or the cure but on 
the despairometer human drama comes out on top 
indovina yelps favors a sobby vibrato and uses the pained 
hiccup effect in his vocals 
his alienated voice is alienating his songs may have arisen 
from genuinely deep pain but its difficult to share that pain 
with him his lyrics are mostly obscure and cryptic 
send in the undertakers or maybe a psychiatrist 
so deep it burns i burn until i cry i die indovina sings 
on death of an angel then on dying in a moment of 
splendor indovina relates i am an artist with a vision seeing 
hell his destiny and in there is only you indovina sings 
about coming close to suicide though it might be just fantasy 
so johnny feels bad but why 
is it the ozone layer toxic wastes love gone sour addiction 
indovina refers to an inner battle between good and evil which 
could be tied to the struggle with addiction he relates in 
tumble and never never 
references to angels heaven god demons easter the golden 
rule and prayers are sprinkled through feel its too bad a 
little holy water couldnt have been sprinkled too because this 
record sounds anything but celestial 
it takes more courage to sing about inner struggles than about 
cars and girls but indovina lacks the directness of a tracy 
chapman or bruce springsteen that makes the pain personal enough to 
touch the hearts of an audience 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 
smoking in the fields rca the del fuegos 
 
the del fuegos color the world like autumn burnt orange 
russet siena sepia 
on smoking in the fields they sound like theyve been 
through the lighthearted spring and summer and now are living in a 
season where things are more serious and the winds blow harder but 
where flashes of color and cozy blankets give warmth 
ill stand by you when youre feelin tired gray and old 
honey i will be too dan zanes sings on stand by you the 
track is the most strippeddown on the album featuring just zanes 
an acoustic guitar and a little help from unobtrusive strings and 
backing vocals 
most of the rest of this album is barroom stomp rock that would 
be in good company alongside jason and the scorchers or the leroi 
brothers the fuegos get pumped on move with me sister and no 
no never then slow down into the midtempo part of this 
earth and a bluestinted jam on lost weekend 
guitars carry the tunes and tom lloyds bass is mixed up high 
enough to give a weighty feel horns add brightness but harmonica 
