<TEXT>
telemundo group inc a spanishlanguage 
television station operator and programmer said monday that its 
president and chief executive henry r silverman plans to resign 
silverman plans to leave the company feb 2 to join the private 
investment banking firm the blackstone group as a general partner 
the announcement said 
he will be replaced as chief executive at telemundo by chairman 
saul steinberg donald g raider will continue to handle daytoday 
management of telemundo as executive vice president and chief 
operating officer 
silverman will remain on the telemundo board and advise the 
company on strategic issues the statement said 
silvermans exertise has been in the mergers and acquisitions 
arena and has been associated with steinberg in two major 
restructurings 
as an officer of reliance capital group a subsidiary of 
steinbergs reliance group holdings inc silverman negotiated the 
600 million acquisition of the days inn of america motel chain in 
1984 he headed days inn until it was sold last year for 765 
million 
he also orchestated the formation of telemundo as a 
spanishlanguage television power telemundo was founded in 
november 1985 and bought a television station in los angeles that 
was converted into a spanishlanguage operation 
in 1986 telemundo acquired john blair amp co a communications 
concern for 600 million telemundo sold all of blairs assets 
except for two spanishlanguage tv stations for 500 million and 
bought additional stations in new york san jose calif and 
houston 
telemundo also acquired a company in miami that distributed 
programming via satellite and it has converted that operation into 
a spanishlanguage tv network through which it supplies programming 
to 31 affiliate stations that reach 77 percent of all hispanic 
households in the united states 
henry has played a key role in the rapid growth of telemundo 
helping to transform our vision for the companmy into a reality 
steinberg said in a news release 
silverman said he decided to move on because his skills are in 
finance and acquisitions and telemundo no longer needs my 
abilities while blackstone group will put them to work 
he said as a principal at blackstone group he will concentrate 
on managing funds that firm has assembled for investment in 
companies recently bought out that have encountered financial 
difficulties or need to be restructured 
blackstones cofounders chairman peter g peterson and 
president stephen a schwarzman said silvermans addtion to the 
firm adds another dimension to our financial services 
blackstone group provides a wide spectrum of financial advisory 
services to major industrial corporations and financial 
institutions 
