compaq computer corp will delay shipments of its 
new deskpro 48625 personal computer because of a faulty intel 
corp chip officials said monday it is the second problem found 
in the advanced microprocessor 
about a week ago on monday we were contacted by intel just 
saying that there was an errata discovered in the 486 chip said 
nora rice media relations administrator for the houstonbased 
computer manufacturer 
she said intel said it was working to find a solution to the 
problem but the trouble will delay introduction of the new machine 
we were targeting shipping the computer feb 1 ms rice 
said but with this new errata it will delay the ship date 
its important to understand whats causing the problem 
before you put in a fix or a workaround that configures the 
computer differently she said 
compaq discovered another problem with the advanced chip last 
fall before intel had begun shipping the microprocessor 
when compaq unveiled the deskpro 48625 last november it called 
it the most powerful desktop computer yet 
intels 486 chip introduced last april is so powerful that it 
will allow personal computers to do certain jobs now done by 
engineering workstations minicomputers and even mainframes 
the most recent trouble could affect other computers using the 
extended industry standard architecture or eisa 32bit bus ms 
rice said 
compaq has not released any of its other 486based machines ms 
rice said 
i think they will be delayed but its safe to say they will 
be out within the first quarter 
