resigned monday in what analysts called part of the companys drive 
to resolve problems in switching to a new generation of products 
cupertinobased apple the worlds no 2 personal computer 
maker has faced declining profits for nearly a year mostly due to 
poor us sales 
company officials announced the resignation of allan z loren as 
president of apple usa the companys foundering domestic sales and 
marketing unit loren 51 a former insurance executive once was 
considered a candidate to head the company 
apple has been in a hunkereddown mode since before christmas 
and it is trying to put itself back onto the road and this is a 
message it is making a major move in that direction said richard 
shaffer publisher of new yorkbased technologic computer letter 
michael h spindler 47 president of apple europe was named 
chief operating officer by john sculley chief executive and 
company president 
the new position is designed to help the company improve 
coordination of business operations and streamline daytoday 
activities apple said in a statement 
the companys latest financial results apparently sealed lorens 
fate 
during its latest quarter apple suffered an 11 percent decline 
in profits from a year earlier it was the third straight quarter 
apple experienced a decline in revenue and profits with most of 
the problems centered on the us sales and marketing division the 
companys largest 
apple which had revenues of 53 billion in 1989 said two 
weeks ago it would reduce employment by 5500 mostly through 
attrition and reassignment and would not rule out the possibility 
of layoffs 
it also froze salaries for six months eliminated cars for 
usbased executives and cut back its profitsharing plan 
apple faces a critical year in 1990 from major competitors who 
will be introducing their own graphic interface products which are 
software programs that use symbols to allow the user to tell 
computers what to do 
