on research and development last year compared to apples 8 
percent yet came out with more new computers 
although the personal computer industry in general has been hurt 
by sagging sales the past six months apple also was beset by 
significantly slower us sales of some of its leading product 
lines particularly lowend macintosh models and the apple ii 
personal computers 
many software distributors have been angry over the 
comparatively low level of promotion by apple last christmas for 
its apple ii developed 13 years ago many dealers and owners of 
the machine fear the company is preparing to abandon it in favor of 
the macintosh 
apple also has been hurt by declining sales of peripheral 
equipment because of increased competition and lower minimum 
purchase requirements for major resellers which encouraged the 
companies to order lower volumes lorenzo said 
whats happened is that theyve neglected the lowend of the 
market and concentrated on maintaining or increasing their share of 
the business part of the market said eugene glazer an analyst 
with dean witter reynolds inc of new york 
sales figures by storeboard inc a dallas market researcher 
show that unit sales of apple computers through us dealers 
decreased last year while revenue increased indicating at least 
in part a shift toward more expensive machines 
many of apples longtime customers want the company to put more 
effort into software for its less costly machines and to introduce 
better versions of those products without drastically increasing 
price 
