<TEXT>
black amp decker corp posted a net loss of 
32 million in the final three months of 1989 because of higher 
interest costs and the writeoff of goodwill following its 
acquisition of emhart corp the company announced 
the quarterly loss which amounted to 5 cents a share compared 
with net income of 38 million or 65 cents a share in the same 
period a year earlier 
operating income which is calculated before interest and taxes 
rose 80 percent in the quarter to 116 million reflecting the 
emhart acquisition and doubledigit operating income growth in 
existing black amp decker businesses 
sales rose 60 percent to 11 billion 
the period constitutes a stub period following the decision 
by the power tool and home products company to change in its fiscal 
year end from the last sunday in september to dec 31 
black amp decker aquired emhart a diversified producer of 
industrial and commercial products for 28 billion last spring 
the company also announced it has completed the sale of its 
bostik adhesives business a part of the emhart acquisition to 
orkem sa of france for 345 million proceeds of the sale will be 
used to reduce debt the company said 
the company also plans to sell two other businesses its 
footwear materials unit to united machinery group ltd for 125 
million and its capacitors business excluding the us segment to 
nissei electric co ltd for 80 million both transactions are 
subject to negotiation of final contracts the company said 
</TEXT>
