<TEXT>
america west airlines has ordered two boeing 
747400s and taken options on two more boeing commercial airplanes 
said monday 
the order along with spare parts and training is worth about 
280 million boeing said 
america west based in phoenix plans to use the jumbo jets on 
flights to hawaii engines for the new planes have not yet been 
chosen 
boeing now has received orders for 246 of the longrange 
747400s from 26 customers 
