<DOCNO> AP900129-0268 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
an investment group said it intends to wage a 
proxy fight to gain control of national intergroup inc a 
pittsburghbased holding company 
centaur partners iv based in new york said monday in filings 
with the securities and exchange commission that it and other 
investors have acquired 1653 percent of niis stock and hope to 
restructure or sell the company 
the move was seen as hostile by nii which issued a statement 
saying centaur partners have nothing to add to the existing 
restructuring program which the company has been actively pursuing 
for the past year 
the company said it already had sold its aluminum fabrication 
businesses for 135 million and made progress in negotiating the 
sale of the rest of its aluminum and steel operations the company 
plans to concentrate its operations on pharmaceuticals and oil 
nii said it expects a significant increase in earnings in fiscal 
1990 
also monday centaur asked the delaware chancery court to 
prevent nii from triggering a poison pill antitakeover device 
the technique would allow nii to issue stock purchase rights to 
shareholders 10 days after a hostile investor gains a stake of 10 
percent or more in the company 
niis stock which has swung widely in value during the past 
year because of takeover speculation lost 2 a share monday to 
close at 1562 on the new york stock exchange 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

